17
00:00:40,530 --> 00:00:43,770
But, that’s going to change!

18
00:00:43,770 --> 00:00:45,550
Because in this new budget proposal

19
00:00:45,550 --> 00:00:47,160
from the Pentagon for 2020

20
00:00:47,160 --> 00:00:50,170
they’re requesting nearly 50 billion more—

21
00:00:50,170 --> 00:00:53,590
putting it at almost 720 billion dollars.

22
00:00:53,590 --> 00:00:54,590
To give you an idea,

23
00:00:54,590 --> 00:00:56,750
that’s more than the next 6 countries’

24
00:00:56,750 --> 00:00:59,280
military budgets combined.

25
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,789
But why spend so much more now?

26
00:01:01,789 --> 00:01:05,350
Well, according to the Acting US Secretary
of Defense,

27
00:01:05,350 --> 00:01:08,509
it’s because of China, China, China.

28
00:01:08,509 --> 00:01:09,509
In a prepared testimony

29
00:01:09,509 --> 00:01:11,899
to the Senate Armed Services Committee,

30
00:01:11,899 --> 00:01:12,899
Shanahan wrote,

31
00:01:12,899 --> 00:01:16,549
“China is aggressively modernizing its military,

32
00:01:16,549 --> 00:01:19,439
systematically stealing science and technology,

33
00:01:19,439 --> 00:01:21,439
and seeking military advantage

34
00:01:21,439 --> 00:01:24,969
through a strategy of military-civil fusion.”

35
00:01:24,969 --> 00:01:26,659
The new budget proposal includes money

36
00:01:26,659 --> 00:01:27,930
for a bunch of things,

37
00:01:27,930 --> 00:01:29,909
like staying ahead of Chinese bombers,

38
00:01:29,909 --> 00:01:32,880
hypersonic weapons, and cyber attacks.

39
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:35,189
It also includes about $14 billion

40
00:01:35,189 --> 00:01:38,779
for space based systems and the Space Force.

41
00:01:38,779 --> 00:01:40,810
Because again, China.

42
00:01:40,810 --> 00:01:42,799
What a great time to be alive.

43
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:43,999
The budget proposal says,

44
00:01:43,999 --> 00:01:47,079
“It is increasingly clear that China and
Russia

45
00:01:47,079 --> 00:01:48,220
want to shape a world

46
00:01:48,220 --> 00:01:51,149
consistent with their authoritarian models—

47
00:01:51,149 --> 00:01:53,639
gaining veto authority over other nations’

48
00:01:53,639 --> 00:01:56,459
economic, diplomatic, and security decisions.”

49
00:01:56,459 --> 00:01:58,770
That’s a concern that the Chairman

50
00:01:58,770 --> 00:02:01,409
of the Joint Chiefs of Staff also shares.

51
00:02:01,409 --> 00:02:03,719
“China and Russia have capitalized on

52
00:02:03,719 --> 00:02:05,169
our distractions and restraints

53
00:02:05,169 --> 00:02:09,509
by investing in capabilities specifically
designed

54
00:02:09,509 --> 00:02:12,450
to challenge our traditional sources of strength.”

55
00:02:12,450 --> 00:02:15,390
I just hope the new military budget includes
the weapon

56
