China.

175
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:29,970
You see Foxconn is actually a Taiwanese company.

176
00:07:29,970 --> 00:07:31,569
And chairman Terry Gou says he might

177
00:07:31,569 --> 00:07:35,180
move some of its work back to Taiwan.

178
00:07:35,180 --> 00:07:37,610
One reason is because the US-China trade war

179
00:07:37,610 --> 00:07:41,600
makes it more expensive to manufacture in
China.

180
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,449
Another reason is, he doesn’t want to be

181
00:07:43,449 --> 00:07:46,540
forced to keep corporate data in China,

182
00:07:46,540 --> 00:07:48,350
under Chinese law.

183
00:07:48,350 --> 00:07:49,800
Although to be fair—

184
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,479
under Chinese law,

185
00:07:51,479 --> 00:07:53,879
Taiwan is just another province of China.

186
00:07:53,879 --> 00:07:56,330
The United States is continuing to put pressure

187
00:07:56,330 --> 00:07:59,250
on Chinese telecom company Huawei.

188
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:01,889
The US has warned countries around the world

189
00:08:01,889 --> 00:08:04,930
that Huawei is working with the Chinese regime

190
00:08:04,930 --> 00:08:07,159
to undermine national security.

191
00:08:07,159 --> 00:08:11,460
Now, the US is giving that warning to Brazil.

192
00:08:11,460 --> 00:08:13,680
The Chinese regime has been pushing Huawei

193
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,729
and its 5G network to Brazil

194
00:08:15,729 --> 00:08:17,389
and dozens of other countries

195
